Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @potatoes{12%ounce}(quartered) (peel if you prefer). Finely chop @chives{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped). Dice @mini cucumber{1}(diced). Dice @tomato{1}(diced).

In a #microwave-safe bowl{}, season potatoes with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add @garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon} and cover with #plastic wrap{}; microwave until tender and steaming, ~{6-7%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Drizzle @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a hot #pan{}; cook chicken until cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{} and cover with #foil{}. Wipe out pan.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan. Cook @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}, and chives, stirring, until sauce is smooth and slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

In a #bowl{}, toss @mixed greens{2%ounce}, cucumber, tomato, and @honey dijon dressing{1.5%ounce}.

Spoon sauce over chicken and potatoes. Serve with salad.